-- Argentine Stock Movers: Petrobras Argentina and YPF Are Active
-- B y   E d u a r d o   T h o m s o n
-- 2012-03-30T15:45:57Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-30/argentine-stock-movers-petrobras-argentina-and-ypf-are-active.html
The following companies are having
unusual price changes in Argentine trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and share prices are as of 12:30 p.m. in Buenos
Aires.  The  Merval (MERVAL)  Index rose 0.2 percent to 2,664.22.  Petrobras Argentina SA (PESA)   gained 1.3 percent to 6.97
pesos. The Argentine unit of Brazil’s state-controlled Petroleo
Brasileiro SA rose along with gains in the price of crude.  YPF SA (YPFD)   retreated 0.4 percent to 148.5 pesos after
advancing 3.9 percent yesterday when it announced oil
discoveries. Argentina’s securities regulator will probe recent
trading in YPF stock because of increased volatility, Cronista
Comercial reported, citing a statement from the regulator.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Eduardo Thomson in Santiago at 
